      "content": "A **Reactor** is the Powerhouse backend service (node) in the network. When you run `ph vetra --watch`, a local Reactor starts automatically. Reactors provide:\n\n- Document storage and hosting\n- Document synchronization across clients\n- Conflict resolution\n- Operation history verification (by rerunning operations)\n- GraphQL API for data access\n\nReactors can be configured for:\n- Local storage (development/Studio Mode)\n- Centralized cloud storage\n- Decentralized storage networks\n\nThe Reactor exposes several GraphQL subgraphs: system, analytics, document-editor, vetra-package, subgraph-module, processor-module, app-module, and vetra-read-model. It also provides a WebSocket server for subscriptions and an MCP server for AI agent integration.",
